;But the king gave the crown to Hesiod, declaring that it was right that he who called upon men to follow peace and husbandry should have the prize rather than one who dwelt on war and slaughter&quot;<br />\n<br />\n可以參考：<br />\na. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contest_of_Homer_and_Hesiod\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FContest_of_Homer_and_Hesiod&d=qXcR1A%2FTALq%2FhnoNE0cJVQCffgmrlYx1zcVg66SIO7I%3D&h=5973f275\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contest_of_Homer_and_Hesiod</a><br />\nb. 《競賽》原文英譯<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.sacred-texts.com/cla/homer/homrhes.htm\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sacred-texts.com%2Fcla%2Fhomer%2Fhomrhes.htm&d=qXcR1A%2FTALq%2FhnoNE0cJVQCffgmrlYx1zcVg66SIO7I%3D&h=16bb9888\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.sacred-texts.com/cla/homer/homrhes.htm</a><br />\n<br />\n2.讀《悲劇的誕生》係好耐之前既事﹐但我記得下文尼采自己有分析﹐荷馬(希臘人)係點樣由否定人生開始﹐用史詩、悲劇既精神黎肯定人生。<br />\n<br />\n所以朱文之後既詮釋「那麼我們就要放棄對於幸福的追求嗎？與其說是放棄對於美好的生活狀態的想像，倒不如說尼采反對的幸福是那種建立在知識體系之上的幸福觀....」講得幾好﹐不過好似跳開左原文黎講。<br />\n<br />\n另外﹐《悲劇的誕生》係尼采早期作品﹐好多思想都未成熟的。<br />\n<br />\n有心思駁人﹐寫完篇paper再講啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T01:04:10.000Z","msg":"多謝補充<br />\n<br />\n原作者係回應留言 講 命運之愛 嘅時候<br />\n有提到佢點樣看待 悲劇的誕生 喺尼采著作入面嘅地位<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=4439368086074716&amp;id=100000047068530&amp;comment_id=4441173912560800&amp;reply_comment_id=4441277552550436\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fpermalink.php%3Fstory_fbid%3D4439368086074716%26id%3D100000047068530%26comment_id%3D4441173912560800%26reply_comment_id%3D4441277552550436&d=qXcR1A%2FTALq%2FhnoNE0cJVQCffgmrlYx1zcVg66SIO7I%3D&h=26344f5d\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/permalink.php?story_fbid=4439368086074716&amp;id=100000047068530&amp;comment_id=4441173912560800&amp;reply_comment_id=4441277552550436</a><br />\n// 但是尼采也不是把早期論點全部回收，例如他在《悲劇的誕生》裡面有一個創見是提出「酒神&mdash;&mdash;日神」的二元問題，因為傳統都過度提告太陽神對於文化的影響作用，而尼采認為唯有考慮到酒神那種非理性、迷醉、醜陋、詩性、抗爭、自然狀態等屬性，才能夠更加完整<br />\n而酒神與日神的結合最終的目標會通往個體化原則與權力意志，把主客對立問題消解之後，不再認為我與世界是分裂且對立的，我的自我也是統一且整體的，這才會誕生命運之愛//"},{"pid":"7532cfa103718986825f0a2577d6df114e1dcc6c","tid":2366998,"uid":41458,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"62943e24d02469306c1c3f30a7f14c6784d91d56","tid":2366998,"uid":48631,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-15T04:13:16.000Z","msg":"老高條垃圾講乜錯乜<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T01:15:26.000Z","msg":"佢全部都係一知半解咁講<br />\n但又咁多人睇，知咗佢d 人就慘囉"},{"pid":"b1beee91867a6bbc1f82531a3eeea14f783019c6","tid":2366998,"uid":41458,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"7f45a49e119dd0c91c278d722255951efab980b7","tid":2366998,"uid":66716,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-01-15T06:43:09.000Z","msg":"條肥閪content farm老高 條條片都幾m views 真心唔明<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T01:16:20.000Z","msg":"係，屌那星，content farm到咁都咁多人睇<br />\n入面勁多誇張失實"},{"pid":"a56b00023ad06d0b8aa9d6b919910b76f99dded5","tid":2366998,"uid":173852,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"11590ed424f8a9cc0ba4a8c8702731e43632eb0e","tid":2366998,"uid":138409,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"c327e80a41d83069b10a064c533ef7cb32d71c27","tid":2366998,"uid":173852,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-01-15T23:31:03.000Z","msg":"//關於痛苦的學說，尼采相信一個來自古希臘神話的遙遠傳說，他在《悲劇的誕生》指出：「人生最大的幸福對人類來說，已經是達不到：就是從未出生、不存在；第二幸福對人類來講就是&mdash;&mdash;早點死去！」那麼我們就要放棄對於幸福的追求嗎？與其說是放棄對於美好的生活狀態的想像，倒不如說尼采反對的幸福是那種建立在知識體系之上的幸福觀.....//<br />\n<br />\n<span class=\"red\">其實依度都錯左:</span><br />\n<br />\n1.「人生最大的幸福....」一句